reviews_data.review_text: Immediately drawn into the establishment with the warmth of many plants and the nice big tables. We sat at the bar and was immediately acknowledged by the server.  Unfortunately, coming in on a Sunday they were out of the two beers we wanted to try.  We found another selection and were pleasantly surprised.  The place had a really nice, super clean and charming atmosphere. .   The server gave us food recommendations at the Mill and offered us Halloween candy on departure.   We would stop here again.

I am very disappointed in how the manager carried herself. On Sunday morning my Wife and went to Ruby Sunday's around the corner during closed hours of HopFly. Upon returning to our vehicles  everything was very threating to tow. We did not know there was a special event that day. We were told is was written on a sandwich board, well that sandwich board was laying down. The reason I know it was laying down because we saw the blue truck that hit it, however we did not enter from the road but the ally, So I never checked it. I also checked the front door for anything and I saw closed, and hours of operation, which we respected. I do not think that threating to too tow our vehicles was nice, nor Infront of our kids, or shouting across the drive isle at us. A 1 minute conversation would have went along way, but you were more inclined to tow a family car not from southend. In the end do not think that we harmed or inhibited you all for your event either for you were in the very early stages of setting up. If you care that much about an event. I think more than a sandwich board should be thought out and the placement of it probably shouldn't be where it was.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for enjoying our brews! We apologize for the experience with Cool Idiot Coffee. If you wouldn't mind sending an email to ryan@hopflybrewing.com to discuss the coffee encounter a bit more, that would be much appreciated.
reviews_data.review_text:
we visited from asheville and this was such a great experience on the beer side! lots of options, their hoppy choices were  my favorite.

i did have a strange encounter with the person who works at their new coffee shop inside of the brewery. i was excited as this pop up was brewing coffee that is local to us in asheville. but the vibes were extremely tense, and the person working behind the counter was asking alot of personal questions that made us uncomfortable.
aside from that aspect of the space, it was a really great experience! I feel like working and Coffee requires people to read the room a little bit and this person  Was very overbearing it was so unfortunate

reviews_data.review_text:
We travel quite a bit, and everywhere we go we try and find the best breweries in every city.  HopFly is truly one of the best we’ve found in Charlotte. The location is great, the footprint is chill, clean, and comfortable. A unique twist on the ambiance of a brewery here. Hard to explain, but you’ll understand once you’re here.

The beer is top notch. Especially if ipa’s or sours are your sweet spot.  If we return to Charlotte (and we hope to), we’ll be back!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Happy to have such a well-rounded taplist, and happier when people get to enjoy as much as possible! Cheers!
reviews_data.review_text: Beers are fantastic no matter what style you get from lagers to sours always a hit.
Very nice menu and very nice staff but the ac doesn’t work in the back or near the entrance so it was very hot but they have free water cups which is nice

reviews_data.owner_answer: Cheers to that! 🍻
reviews_data.review_text: Hopfly Brewing is a decent spot to try out some local beers. It's not too far from the Uptown area, and the space is pretty large (indoor and outdoor seating). They have lots of food trucks, and the tap list is pretty extensive too (along with having other drinks like cocktails and non-alcoholic beverages for others). Overall a good brewery!
Neat little microbrewery just south of the stadium. Fun ambiance and good beer.

Can’t go wrong with any of their beer.  Unique beer, good location, knowledgeable and kind staff.

Come here often as a local but always bring out of town guest and they love it just as much.
The beer flight was great and they had some very unique beer options. The live music was nice and everything was a great price for the quality as well.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for feedback and glad you enjoyed the food and the vibes. Hope to see you soon. Cheers
reviews_data.review_text: Food truck is good. I recommend the burgers. When there is a DJ there it is way too loud. Can’t hear people next to you talking. Then inside it is very crowded. But the vibe is great.
Love, love, love this place. Great people, amazing selection of very solid brews, and a welcoming environment.
Good beer selection, knowledgeable staff able to talk beer,  Trivia night was fun and food truck had good food and was easy to order and they deliver to table (EASY!)   10 of us went and was fun.

HopFly is more than just a brewery—it’s a community-focused space with great beer and even better people. As the resident DJ, I’ve had the privilege of playing private events, CLT FC & Panthers tailgates, and every set is met with an incredible atmosphere. The taproom, brew house, and my personal favorite—the indoor/outdoor rooftop patio—all create the perfect setting for any gathering. Cam leads with a clear vision, and Anna does an excellent job coordinating events and opportunities. The staff—Jackie, Farr, Jeb, and Jameson—make every visit feel welcoming with their dedication and energy. I even choose to host my own private events here because the space and hospitality are unmatched. Whether you're grabbing a drink or planning an event, HopFly is a true Charlotte gem! #HopFlyCLT #GreatBeerGreatPeople
Chill space with great beers. Bartender was engaged. Food truck that we could order from the table.
Awesome place! Great beer selections and super atmosphere.
Visiting from LA and found this brewery.  I was looking for an IPA and I found an excellent one.  Dabs!!  Highly recommend.
Loved that they had other drink options other than just beer. Great space, very open, nice staff
Excellent beer quality.  Food truck was great. Only thing we didn't like was the DJ...too loud.

We held our wedding welcome party at the Loft & Terrace at Hopfly Brewing on October 25, 2024. Would 100% recommend Hopfly for any upcoming events. They were super easy to work with leading up to and on the day of the event. Jameson & Jackie rocked the bar all night and kept the drinks flowing all night! So happy we chose Hopfly to host our welcome party!
Good beer. Nice staff. Cool views of Charlotte.
Great beer, great bar tenders!

Before heading to the Saints tailgate, I swung by HopFly for a drink and grabbed some food from Sure Fire. I was blown away by how tasty and well-prepared everything was! The food had great flavor and quality that really exceeded my expectations. HopFly is now a must-stop whenever I’m in Charlotte—amazing beer, delicious food!
Beautiful space, lovely patio and absolutely the BEST pastry sour I have ever tasted.  The Peach Cobbler Pastry Sour is EXCEPTIONAL!

Had a great time this past weekend at Hopfly ! Not only is the brews always on point, but the food truck they had there was something special. The smash burger I had was right up there with Harriet’s—easily the best food I’ve had here since KatsuCart left (still hurting). It’d be amazing to see this truck around more often. Definitely a perfect fit for the area.
Cool Atmosphere Great Beers and Good Music
Great atmosphere and great beer selection!

Hopfly is one of my all time favorite breweries and I love their IPA's! I had a wonderfully relaxing Sunday afternoon here a couple weeks ago; can't wait to go back!
Great patio and nice atmosphere inside! Beer was good as well.

I tried a few beers, the food truck sadly was closed when we went but they were very accommodating with us getting outside food. Seems they have some events that happen regularly, including a cycling group. The bartender was informative and had no problems answering specific questions. Even let me know which beers were vegan for me to take some home to my wife. Amazing selections.

The beer is exquisite, especially if you like hazy IPAs, but more importantly:  HOPFLY WENT COMPLETELY OUT OF THEIR WAY, to get me my cell phone back.   Its a long story but I would of had to cancel a trip had the management/staff not gone above and beyond their duties to get me my phone back.  I think in 2023 you rarely see people that care this much.   I am so grateful

Great beers, great atmosphere, clean tap room, nice staff.

;)

Solid brews. Great views. Friendly staff. What else could you want?
Great space. Very crowded but fast and friendly bartenders. Nice selection of beers.

I love what they did with the remodel of the current space. Always been a fan of their beers and it's great to welcome them into Charlotte! One of the best views of the city and now with more amazing floor space both inside and outside to enjoy beers.
Hands down best brewery in NC and so excited they've come to Charlotte... looking forward to grabbing many a brew here!!

reviews_data.review_text: Immediately drawn into the establishment with the warmth of many plants and the nice big tables. We sat at the bar and was immediately acknowledged by the server.  Unfortunately, coming in on a Sunday they were out of the two beers we wanted to try.  We found another selection and were pleasantly surprised.  The place had a really nice, super clean and charming atmosphere. .   The server gave us food recommendations at the Mill and offered us Halloween candy on departure.   We would stop here again.

I am very disappointed in how the manager carried herself. On Sunday morning my Wife and went to Ruby Sunday's around the corner during closed hours of HopFly. Upon returning to our vehicles  everything was very threating to tow. We did not know there was a special event that day. We were told is was written on a sandwich board, well that sandwich board was laying down. The reason I know it was laying down because we saw the blue truck that hit it, however we did not enter from the road but the ally, So I never checked it. I also checked the front door for anything and I saw closed, and hours of operation, which we respected. I do not think that threating to too tow our vehicles was nice, nor Infront of our kids, or shouting across the drive isle at us. A 1 minute conversation would have went along way, but you were more inclined to tow a family car not from southend. In the end do not think that we harmed or inhibited you all for your event either for you were in the very early stages of setting up. If you care that much about an event. I think more than a sandwich board should be thought out and the placement of it probably shouldn't be where it was.

aside from that aspect of the space, it was a really great experience! I feel like working and Coffee requires people to read the room a little bit and this person  Was very overbearing it was so unfortunate

reviews_data.review_text:
We travel quite a bit, and everywhere we go we try and find the best breweries in every city.  HopFly is truly one of the best we’ve found in Charlotte. The location is great, the footprint is chill, clean, and comfortable. A unique twist on the ambiance of a brewery here. Hard to explain, but you’ll understand once you’re here.

The beer is top notch. Especially if ipa’s or sours are your sweet spot.  If we return to Charlotte (and we hope to), we’ll be back!

Good beer selection, knowledgeable staff able to talk beer,  Trivia night was fun and food truck had good food and was easy to order and they deliver to table (EASY!)   10 of us went and was fun.

HopFly is more than just a brewery—it’s a community-focused space with great beer and even better people. As the resident DJ, I’ve had the privilege of playing private events, CLT FC & Panthers tailgates, and every set is met with an incredible atmosphere. The taproom, brew house, and my personal favorite—the indoor/outdoor rooftop patio—all create the perfect setting for any gathering. Cam leads with a clear vision, and Anna does an excellent job coordinating events and opportunities. The staff—Jackie, Farr, Jeb, and Jameson—make every visit feel welcoming with their dedication and energy. I even choose to host my own private events here because the space and hospitality are unmatched. Whether you're grabbing a drink or planning an event, HopFly is a true Charlotte gem! #HopFlyCLT #GreatBeerGreatPeople
Chill space with great beers. Bartender was engaged. Food truck that we could order from the table.

So happy we chose Hopfly to host our welcome party!

Definitely a perfect fit for the area.
